ove 92%. Across nine months of the year 380 matches are viewed in 212 territories worldwide. Coverage of the matches is available in approximately 804m households.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">The Football Foundation – providing facilities for mor</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">e girls and women to play sport</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Football Foundation is the largest sports charity in the UK funded by the Premier League, The FA and Government (via Sport England). It funds the development of new and refurbished grassroots sports facilities improving </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the quality and experience of playing sport at the grassroots level to sustain and increase participation and improve general skills levels.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In the twelve years that the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Football Foundation </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">has been in existence, the Premier League has </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">invested £200m into </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the organisation. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In that time the Foundation has supported 9,611 projects with grants worth £410.4m. These grants have helped leverage in over £564m in additional inward investment.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In specific reference to one of the Committee’s questions as part of this Inquiry, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">on </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the availability of facilities for women and girls to play sport, the Premier League and its partners are making every effort through the Foundation to create new and bet</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ter </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">public sports </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">facilities for women to play on. Whilst there is obviously only so much any one organisation can do, we firmly believe that through grants given to build new facilities (or refurbish existing ones), the Football Foundation is making a sig</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nificant difference in providing quality facilities for female players. The statistics bear this out:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger