<li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Rachel Pavlou, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">the National Women’s Football Development Manager for The Football Association, was also impressed by wha</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">t she saw at Anfield.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">"My role is about developing girls' football so it was just brilliant when coming here to have the first thing I see are four pitches of girls playi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ng the game.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> The standard looks really good. The organisation of the tournament has be</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">en fantastic and truly professional.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">"I am just really pleased that girls get the chance to play on this fantastic pitch at the same time as the boys do. They are getting the same opportunities, which is exactly what we want. There are some really good pla</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">yers and what is really impressive is that the girls’ game is improving every year. You can see that here each year."</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Premier League 4 Sport</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> (PL4S)</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">PL4S uses the power of Premier League football club brands to engage and encourage children to actively part</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">icipate in a range of Olympic sports, and recently received a boost in the form of a new £16.8m partnership between the Premier League and Sport England.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> The programme is having a hugely positive impact on getting young people into sports that they may not</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> have the opportunity to play through their normal school networks, and is helping Olympic sports who have struggled to engage and retain young people. </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The project has recently</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">seen </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">golf, tennis, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">boxing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and athletics being added to the eight Olympic, Paralympic and Commonwealth sports on offer through PL4Sport</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> (these are badminton, judo, table tennis, volleyball, basketball, handball, hockey and netball). </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Premier League clubs link up, through the Olympi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">c sports’ governing bodies, with local sports clubs. Through the football clubs well-established community links with schools, they offer taster session in these sports, run inter-club competitions in the various sports (with teams taking part in the strip</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s of the Premier League football club) and give youngsters the opportunity to move into coaching in each of these sports too. 351 sports clubs now link with their local PL clubs, and 60,000 young people have participated in these Olympic sports through the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> PL4Sport project, with 21,600 (36%) being female. This is a particularly impressive number given the fact that research shows that girls often look to give up sport in their teenage years, whereas through PL4S a significant number are being retained by th</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">e Olympic sports they are trying out.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Sasha Corbin, the England netball captain, underlined the importance of the programme in engaging girls:</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">"It's brilliant to get girls involved in sport especially from netball's perspective. It's great to have the comm</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">unity projects that have a football team so they can feel a part of something. </span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">"It will help to get more girls playing because our drop-out </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">rate starts when they leave </span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">school and it's</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> all about keeping them engaged with these projects</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">We're hoping that </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">his is the link, this will help and the more money that is pumped into it the more girls that can get involved."</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">PL4S also engages young disabled participants. A good example is Felicity Pickard, a 17 year old with cerebral palsy, who </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">was spotted by Hyndbu</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rn table tennis club in Accrington through</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">a PL4S session she took part in at Blackburn Rovers. She had never played before coming to table tennis through PL4S, but it is has now transformed her life and she now volunteers at the club, is a Level 1 coach a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">nd trains with Paralympian GB coaches. She is seen as ‘an incredible role model’ by the PL4S co-ordinator at Blackburn Rovers.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Sports have sought to modify their sessions to appeal to girls. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Through the innovation of clubs working on this project they have</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> been able </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">to open the sport up to females. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Stoke City FC are a prime example of this. To get more women engaged in their Table Tennis sessions, they spoke to young people about what it would take to get them involved. They decided the environment needed t</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">o be friendlier, welcoming and more about them. The atmosphere of the session changed entirely, the music was cranked up, the social element was magnified and the girls organised to buy their own pink bats. This led to the session being one of the first fe</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">male only sessions run by PL4S.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Derby County’s ‘The Movement’ project</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Premier League / Professional Footballers’ Association (PL/PFA) Fund is set up to support individual Premier League and Football League club projects that work with local partners to meet specific local objectives. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Through the PL/PFA fund we support a</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> wide range of projects that help younger and older females take part in sport. This ranges from specific activities designed to get more young females involved in sport, through to open activities where females are encouraged and supported to be involved.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">One example is the PL/PFA funded project that was run by Derby County, the Movement which was set up in partnership with the Council to promote physical activity amongst teenagers, particularly females. The project has proved so successful it has now bee</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n adopted as a key part of Derby City Council’s Sport Development strategy, so has become truly sustainable. One highlight saw d</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ancers and a singer performing at the Olympic Park as part of London 2012 celebrations. The girls aged between 12 and 18, entert</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ained people waiting or moving between events in the south of the park near to the iconic Olympic Stadium and Orbit art structure. Jeremy Sainter from the Olympic </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">entertainment team claimed that The Movement attracted the biggest crowd of all the dance per</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">formances with around 1,000 people clapping and cheering the girls on. </span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Movement - recognised by London 2012's Inspire programme for its work in helping young people lead healthy lifestyles - joined one of only four projects in the Midlands to perform </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">at Olympic Park.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Chantelle Richards (18) from Littleover, who danced solo said: </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“Just being there was surreal but dancing for London 2012 is an unbelievable experience. People seemed to enjoy our performances and there was a real buzz everywhere.”</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Natalie </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">York (16) also from St Benedict's said: </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“The atmosphere was fantastic and it was packed full of smiley people. We attracted a decent amount of people to watch us at each performance.”</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Sharon Dale, The Movement's Project Manager believes their involvement i</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">n London 2012 would inspire other youngsters: </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“It was a momentous day for The Movement and all the girls involved. We are delighted to be part of such an historic event and showcase Derby’s young talent on an international scale. We hope it inspires more y</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">oung people to join The Movement’s wide range of activity opportunities.”</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">More info: </span><a href="http://www.derbycountycommunitytrust.com/the-movement/about.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.derbycountycommunitytrust.com/the-movement/about.html</span></a></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusions</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The Premier League is playing a substantial part in not only funding </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">grassroots facilities that are allowing more women and girls to play sport, but is investing heavily in projects that are targeting large numbers of female participants.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Given the aims an</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">d objectives of Premier League 4 Sport, this is not limited to only football either, with twelve Olympic sports benefiting from working with Premier League clubs.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We would be very happy to organise for a visit to see a project in which there are particular</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">ly high numbers of women taking part in community-level sport so as to help the Committee in its</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Inquiry. With a large number of the PL clubs delivering this work within close proximity of Westminster, any visit could be accommodated within a couple of hou</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">rs of MPs’ time, and would greatly enhance their understanding of how professional football is working to make a significant difference in this hugely important area.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>